The JIRA system can be used to converse about issues.  This is a nice way to track a threaded conversation -- much better than email.  Sometimes the set of posts can be very long.  It would be nice to number the posts in order to refer to them.  For example, it would be nice to say something like "see Bob's post #12 in issue XYZ-42.  

Further, it would be nice to be able to link to individual posts using post ids.  Yes, I know you can create or access a permanent link to each post, but that's not useful in a conversation. Instead of an obscure sequence of letters and numbers, posts could be referenced using the issue number and the post number.  For example, XYZ-42.12 would refer to post #12 in issue YXZ-42.

Thanks for considering this for a future release.

