In the new version of the workflow designer, the old common transitions have been incorporated into the "Reuse a transition" tab.  I am very glad to see the feature being added to the new designer.  The one drawback I've noticed about the way that it has been implemented is that the transition id numbers are no longer listed next to the transition names like they were in the classic designer.  This becomes problematic when you have multiple transitions with the same name but different properties leading to the same destination step.  If you want to make a transition common with one of those, there is no good way to figure out the proper transition to choose.  Your only choices are trial and error or temporarily editing your transition names.

In short, I'd like to see the transition ids added to the "Transition to reuse" dropdown on the "Reuse a transition" tab.

