Agile has a {{AboutPagePanelModuleDescriptor}} that tries to parse {{[^bom.csv]}} from inside the plugin. However, when this happens we get this warning in the logs.

{noformat}
2014-04-22 14:10:32.233025500 2014-04-22 14:10:32,232 TP-Processor8 INFO sysadmin 850x3003x1 1e6rga7 59.167.133.1,59.167.29.201 /secure/AboutPage.jspa [jira.plugin.aboutpagepanel.BomParserImpl] Could not parse license info line: ColorPickerbyDHTMLGoodies.com,Unspecified,GNU Lesser General Public License 2.1,,binary,
{noformat}

The problem is that our parser assumes there will only be 5 CSV entries, however, all in the agile {{bom.csv}} have 6. I am not sure if JIRA's parser is broken or if Agile is generating an invalid {{bom.csv}}. In their case I think our parser should be a little more robust (i.e. just ignore any extra fields).

